# Jobs CRM Project Rules

## Project Overview
Professional Jobs CRM system with admin and user interfaces. UI-first approach with dynamic functionality.

## Technical Stack
- **Frontend**: HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript (Vanilla)
- **Backend**: PHP (XAMPP environment)
- **Database**: MySQL
- **Real-time**: WebSockets (no polling intervals)
- **UI Framework**: Custom responsive design

## Core Features

### Admin Panel
- Job creation with required fields
- SLA (Service Level Agreement) time setting
- Job management dashboard
- Vendor management
- Chat system per vendor

### User Interface
- Jobs listing page
- Individual job view with details
- Add vendor functionality per job
- Vendor-specific chat areas
- Real-time notifications based on SLA

### Database Structure
- Jobs table (id, title, description, sla_time, status, created_at)
- Vendors table (id, job_id, name, contact, details, created_at)
- Messages table (id, job_id, vendor_id, sender_type, message, timestamp)
- Users table (id, username, role, created_at)

## UI/UX Guidelines
- Modern, clean interface
- Responsive design (mobile-first)
- Professional color scheme
- Intuitive navigation
- Real-time updates without page refresh
- Chat interface similar to modern messaging apps

## Development Approach
1. **Phase 1**: Professional UI/UX design
2. **Phase 2**: Dynamic JavaScript functionality
3. **Phase 3**: PHP backend integration
4. **Phase 4**: Database implementation
5. **Phase 5**: Real-time features with WebSockets

